node.text:
We finally got around to making an “official” 😜video for The Marriage Journal. So here we are👋🏻 telling you how it works and why you need to start this weekly journal now!

We’ve been doing our marriage journal for 6 years and it continues to be one of the best things for our marriageeach week, and has become especially vital since having kids😉 

Each week starts off with an very short encouraging devotional that will invite meaningful conversations, followed by a calendar section to help you get on the same page going into the week,  and then follows the real magic of the journal - the 6 questions you ask each other and record your answers to each week. 

Want to have more meaningful connection and communication with to your spouse, understand them better, dream together and grow in love? Go grab your copy of The Marriage Journal while it’s still 20% off (Black Friday sale ends 11/30 at midnight). 

themarriagejournal.com

Pssstttt if you’ve been doing this journal for a while now, sound off in the comments with how it’s blessed your marriage!🙏🏻

We hear it all the time from people who start The Marriage Journal - they only wish they would have started it sooner. It doesn’t matter if your marriage is thriving or hanging on by a thred, this is a tool for you❤️

node.text:
You helped us raise $34,000 for @feedingamerica 🙌🏻 WOW! A couple weeks ago we brought back these ‘love more’ sweatshirts with a mission help raise money for COVID relief. When we brought them back we told y’all that we planned to donate 50% of the profits to @feedingamerica so that your purchase of a love more sweatshirt would actually represent an act of loving more! Every $1 donated to Feeding America = 10 meals! That means you all helped provide 340,000 meals to families in need😭 We are so honored and humbled that we could be the catalyst for such an amazing gift. This money will help people get meals and food who are unable to do so during this difficult time. We are getting to work right away on your sweatshirt and we hope these help remind you to love more not just everyday, but to everybody as well. ⁣
⁣
Thank youuuuuuu!😭 #lovemore

node.text:
Exactly one year ago we were waking up in New York City at the crack of dawn to kick off a 3 week book tour around the country (lol at how opposite life looks right now#stayhome 😂) ⁣
⁣
For years leading up to the release of this book we prayed for it to impact love stories around the world in a way that would inspire them to pursue a love that is creative, intentional, and faithful. We asked God to inspire our writing as well as your reading. We had a big goal/dream to become New York Times best-selling authors and to get this book in the hands of 100,000 people within the first year of its life. And praise God for answering those prayers in abundance😭 We are so encouraged by the messages we receive from single people, dating couples, newlyweds, and couples married for decades🤯 This book has met so many people exactly where they are at in their love story, and motivated them to live the love story they would want to have read back to them one day. So THANK YOU for cheering on this little-engine-that-could book and sharing it with your friends, family, and followers🙏🏻 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Today in honor of the one year anniversary of A Love Letter Life we are going to be going live reading parts of the book, talking with some of you about how the book has impacted your life story, and playing A Love Letter Life trivia edition of our “Quarentime” game!😜 Were also doing a fun giveaway today for those of you who share about A Love Letter Life on your IG today 👉🏻 deets over on @beating50percent ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Drop a 💌below if A Love Letter Life has impacted your love story👇🏻 #ALoveLetterLife

node.title: TODAY IS A SPECIAL DAY!💌 It’s A Love Letter Life’s 1st birthday!!!🎉

node.text:
If you’ve been following me for a while you know how hard of a decision this was for me... ⁣
⁣
And if you’re newer around here, here is a little bit of context. ⁣
⁣
I was a distance runner in high school and college and I used to write two words on my hand before every race:⁣
⁣
ALWAYS MORE⁣
⁣
These words, inspired by Ephesians 3:20, reminded me to ALWAYS believe in the MORE that was within me through Christ. But what started as a motivational running reminder became so much MORE than I ever imagined it would - pun intended😉⁣
⁣
Over the past 15 years, ALWAYS MORE has not only been a life mantra for me, but it has also become a community, a clothing line, and a source of hope, inspiration, and encouragement to women around the world. I’ve read countless stories about how ALWAYS MORE has helped so many of you through loss, heartbreaking diagnosis’s, mental illness, miscarriages, becoming a mom, athletics, starting a business, or pursing a dream. WOW GOD😭 again, more than I ever imagined. ⁣
⁣
Four years ago we designed some ALWAYS MORE sweatshirts and tees which y’all loved so much that we quickly grew into a full online retail shop with the hope of further spreading the ALWAYS MORE message. It became more than I imagined it would be from an impact standpoint🙏🏻, but also from a work standpoint.😅⁣
⁣
All this to say, as I step more fully into this new season of life as a mom with two littles, I need to take a step back from some things that demand a lot of my time. So after lots of discussion, prayer, and tears, I’ve decided to close the shop side of Always More for the foreseeable future.⁣
⁣
So if you’ve been wanting to grab something from our shop for a while, this is your last chance. Details for the shop closure will be over on @shopalwaysmore or alwaysmore.com.⁣
⁣
I hope this doesn’t stop any of you from spreading the ALWAYS MORE message. The beautiful thing about encouragement is that it’s free to give, but it could be of infinite worth to the person receiving it. And that’s what I hope ALWAYS MORE will always be. ⁣#alwaysmore

node.text: BBQ, elephant ears, animals, rides, music, browsing vendor booths, and games that steal your money😂 I grew up going to the fair every year with my family so it’s fun to now see my own kids experience it🤗 Ember went on her first roller coaster ride and loved it! We stayed up way past bedtime and the kids fell asleep the second we put them in the car to drive home, but I def woke them up for a quick bath before bed🤪 What is your favorite part about the fair?🎡🎢 🐄🐖🐑🍦🌭🧸🪕

node.text: Thank you to everyone near and far for  making my 30th birthday so special🤗 I’m feeling so blessed by the kind words, encouragement, affirmation, and truth spoken over me the last few days.❤️ Bring on the 30’s!🥂For those of you who are currently in or past this season of life, what was/has been your favorite thing about your thirties?👇🏼

node.text: My dream birthday came to life💃🏼🤠🥃🥳Dress up, drinks, dessert, and country line dancing the night away with friends and fam to celebrate the big 3-0. I like getting people out of their comfort zones a little bit… but especially when they end up having an absolute BLAST!🥳 It was such a joy to see the people I love come together and come alive - laughing, dancing late into the night, and having the freakin best time! My heart is so full (and my hips are so sore🤪). Thank you @alphaazn11 for responding to my DM and coming out to teach a bunch of strangers to line dance for my 30th birthday! It was one of the most fun nights we’ve had in a long time. Jer and I are still practicing our horseshoe today since we had the dance floor for the weekend💃🏼 More epic and hilarious dancing videos to be posted here soon😆Thanks babe for helping bring my vision to life! @jeremyroloff 🤗Tomorrow I’m officially 30, but this weekend of celebration has me feeling crazy blessed over here.❤️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Audrey Mirabella Roloff on July 16, 2021 tagging @jeremyroloff. May be a closeup of 1 person, child and outdoors.

node.text:
Since you were just a few weeks old the Lord nudged me to pray for you that “nothing would steal your joy.” Your name means “messenger,” and I will continue to pray as you get older that you would be a messenger of JOY. That you would live the words of Luke 2:10 “....Fear not, for behold, I bring you good news of great joy that will be for all the people.”

You truly are such a joy Bode bear❤️
